text: Yekaterina Khupovets is a Kazakhstani karateka. In 2014, she won the silver medal in the women's kumite 50 kg event at the 2014 Asian Games held in Incheon, South Korea. In 2010, she competed in the women's kumite 55 kg event at the 2010 Asian Games held in Guangzhou, China without winning a medal. She was eliminated in her first match by Fatemeh Chalaki.
